25:57.924 --> 25:59.759
I know Dad was thinking
about moving out.

25:59.792 --> 26:01.928
I know you weren't happy.
Charlie.

26:01.961 --> 26:04.597
There's nothing I want more than
for us to go to the Galapagos

26:04.631 --> 26:07.099
and all kinds of places.
Okay. Look.

26:07.133 --> 26:08.868
Things are complicated
right now.

26:08.901 --> 26:10.603
We're trying
to figure it out.

26:10.637 --> 26:12.905
And sometimes it is hard
to understand,

26:12.939 --> 26:14.874
and it must make you
feel afraid.

26:14.907 --> 26:16.108
But you're not alone.

26:16.142 --> 26:17.777
I'm not afraid
of being alone.

26:17.810 --> 26:19.679
Lots of kids see
their parents split up.

26:19.712 --> 26:22.749
I'm talking about my father
isn't who you think he is.

26:22.782 --> 26:24.684
He's my father,
but he's not my father

26:24.717 --> 26:26.853
because my father
is a fucking alien.

26:26.886 --> 26:28.020
Charlie.

26:29.922 --> 26:32.124
Enough.

26:40.166 --> 26:41.968
Oh, sorry.

26:42.001 --> 26:43.135
The other.

26:47.073 --> 26:49.308
I hear your dad
is a mutant zombie.

26:49.341 --> 26:51.010
Where did you hear that?

26:51.043 --> 26:52.712
Peretti's brother.

26:52.745 --> 26:54.814
His brother
told my brother.

26:54.847 --> 26:56.082
You okay?

26:56.115 --> 26:58.785
I mean, you are you,
right?

26:58.818 --> 27:01.988
Uh, did he eat
your mother's brains?

27:02.021 --> 27:04.390
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

27:06.759 --> 27:09.896
[SIREN WAILING DISTANTLY]

27:09.929 --> 27:12.631
I guess Dashiell
really did it, huh?

27:14.100 --> 27:15.234
BOY:
Hey!

27:17.704 --> 27:19.338
[SIRENS BLARING]

27:33.352 --> 27:35.922
[***]

27:35.955 --> 27:38.324
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

27:38.357 --> 27:40.727
What's his name?
Philip.

27:48.901 --> 27:50.469
Hey, Philip.

27:50.502 --> 27:52.271
Look, I know you feel
you can't go on,

27:52.304 --> 27:53.806
but things
are gonna get better.

27:53.840 --> 27:56.442
This is only temporary.
I want my wife back.

27:56.475 --> 28:00.379
Well, I wish we could
bring your wife back.

28:00.412 --> 28:02.949
It wasn't right of her
to leave you.

28:02.982 --> 28:06.085
She didn't leave.

28:06.118 --> 28:08.821
She's still there.

28:08.855 --> 28:11.457
But she's not my wife.

28:11.490 --> 28:13.159
Then who is she, Philip?

28:13.192 --> 28:16.128
She's someone. She's--

28:16.162 --> 28:17.964
She's something else.

28:20.800 --> 28:23.936
Okay, look, we can
figure this out. Just--

28:23.970 --> 28:25.972
Just let me help you.

28:28.975 --> 28:30.910
I want you to step
off the ledge, sir.

28:34.046 --> 28:35.915
Step off the ledge, sir.

28:50.930 --> 28:53.232
PRINCIPAL [OVER P.A.]:
Today has been a difficult day.

28:53.265 --> 28:56.302
But just know your teachers
and the administration

28:56.335 --> 28:58.204
will be here all week.

28:58.237 --> 28:59.972
We are here for you.

29:00.006 --> 29:01.774
Man, Dashiell's
gonna be pissed

29:01.808 --> 29:03.509
that he ditched
and missed all this shit.

29:03.542 --> 29:05.511
You wanna go to Superdawg?
No.

29:07.914 --> 29:10.950
In the meantime, we will be
dismissing school by grades.

29:10.983 --> 29:13.953
And your parents have been
notified to pick you up.

29:13.986 --> 29:16.222
For all bus riders,

29:16.255 --> 29:18.791
continue down
the stairs.

29:45.351 --> 29:47.820
[***]

30:58.024 --> 31:00.326
I thought we could
play some ball.

31:00.359 --> 31:03.963
[***]

31:03.996 --> 31:07.299
Charlie, do you know why
they call third base

31:07.333 --> 31:09.001
"the hot corner"?

31:09.035 --> 31:11.103
I know what you are.

31:13.005 --> 31:14.640
Wrong, sir.

31:16.075 --> 31:17.543
Wrong.

31:17.576 --> 31:20.546
It's because when the ball
is hit hard to left-field

31:20.579 --> 31:23.515
and the runner takes off
at a rate of 26 feet per second,

31:23.549 --> 31:26.953
the third baseman has, at most,
three, maybe four seconds

31:26.986 --> 31:30.456
to get the ball
from third to first.

31:30.489 --> 31:32.258
With that short
a margin of error

31:32.291 --> 31:35.161
and the need
for superior reflexes,

31:35.194 --> 31:39.999
third base is the toughest
position in baseball.

31:41.167 --> 31:43.602
Charlie...

31:43.635 --> 31:46.538
can you imagine
what it's like

31:46.572 --> 31:48.975
watching your world
disappear?

31:50.476 --> 31:52.544
Wandering the universe
and star-winds

31:52.578 --> 31:55.147
with no chance
to be with your other?

31:55.181 --> 31:59.151
No chance at progeny?
No chance of a real tomorrow?

32:01.620 --> 32:03.455
It sucks.

32:05.357 --> 32:08.394
But I'm alive now.

32:08.427 --> 32:10.729
I'm here, and it feels right.

32:10.762 --> 32:12.698
And soon, Charlie,
you're gonna be ready.

32:12.731 --> 32:14.666
You're gonna have a chance
to join us.

32:14.700 --> 32:17.469
To become a more perfect
version of yourself.

32:17.503 --> 32:19.538
I will never be like you!

32:23.709 --> 32:26.412
I've been learning a lot
the last couple of days

32:26.445 --> 32:28.414
as I've gotten stronger.

32:30.082 --> 32:32.018
Facts.

32:32.051 --> 32:33.352
Trivia.

32:34.653 --> 32:37.223
Stuff, the whole history
of your kind.

32:37.256 --> 32:39.425
And it wasn't always pretty,
was it?

32:39.458 --> 32:42.361
But with everything
I suck up,

32:42.394 --> 32:45.397
with everything
I breath in,

32:45.431 --> 32:48.167
I keep coming back
to one perplexing,

32:48.200 --> 32:50.236
undeniable conundrum.

32:50.269 --> 32:54.140
And, I mean,
it's baffling me, Charlie.

32:54.173 --> 32:58.110
Half the modern baseball
players bat left-handed.

32:58.144 --> 33:02.014
So why isn't first base
the hot corner too?

33:02.048 --> 33:03.182
Ugh!

33:12.391 --> 33:16.128
[SONG PLAYING INDISTINCTLY
OVER JUKEBOX]

33:30.642 --> 33:33.612
I need to talk to someone
about my father.

33:39.718 --> 33:41.053
[TRAIN PASSING]

33:48.094 --> 33:49.195
[***]

33:49.228 --> 33:50.762
What are we waiting for?

33:50.796 --> 33:53.699
Someone who will know
what to do about this.

33:57.469 --> 33:59.105
Your boss?

34:00.606 --> 34:02.708
MAN: What's your name?
CHARLIE: Charlie.

34:03.775 --> 34:05.111
Charlie.

34:16.322 --> 34:17.589
Hello.

34:17.623 --> 34:20.292
His father
isn't his father.

34:22.128 --> 34:23.729
WOMAN:
I'm Detective Fernandez.

34:23.762 --> 34:25.564
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]
Nancy.

34:27.233 --> 34:28.534
You wanna tell me
about it?

34:28.567 --> 34:31.303
Something's going on.

34:31.337 --> 34:34.306
Something terrible.

34:34.340 --> 34:36.508
Did your father
do something to you?

34:36.542 --> 34:38.644
No, but...

34:38.677 --> 34:40.412
he's not my father.

34:40.446 --> 34:43.349
It's important
to tell the truth.

34:46.185 --> 34:48.554
My father's been replaced.

34:48.587 --> 34:50.489
"Replaced"?

34:52.891 --> 34:56.762
He looks like my father,
but he's not.

34:56.795 --> 34:58.497
Who is he?

34:59.765 --> 35:01.867
A monster.

35:01.900 --> 35:04.136
And where did
this monster come from?

35:04.170 --> 35:05.704
I don't know,
but it's not just him.

35:05.737 --> 35:07.873
It was the neighbors and the
mailman and the UPS man.

35:07.906 --> 35:09.441
Charlie.
But it's not just here.

35:09.475 --> 35:11.710
There are people all over
with the same story.

35:11.743 --> 35:13.745
I understand, Charlie.

35:13.779 --> 35:16.248
You're not the first person
to report

35:16.282 --> 35:19.518
that there's something
going on.

35:20.886 --> 35:23.255
How did you know
my name was Charlie?

35:27.493 --> 35:29.261
Excuse me one second.

35:29.295 --> 35:31.563
[CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

35:32.898 --> 35:35.667
[TRAIN PASSING]

35:35.701 --> 35:37.769
What do you want
to do with him?

35:37.803 --> 35:40.172
We're gonna do
what we gotta do.

36:00.859 --> 36:03.262
[***]

36:38.297 --> 36:39.898
[MOUTHING]
Help me.

36:52.611 --> 36:54.713
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

36:54.746 --> 36:55.914
Dickhead.

36:55.947 --> 36:57.483
HENRY'S MOTHER:
Who is it, Henry?

36:57.516 --> 37:00.286
Dylan's little friend.
What do you want?

37:01.353 --> 37:02.488
I need help.

37:06.558 --> 37:09.295
You better not
be bullshitting us.

37:14.966 --> 37:16.968
CHARLIE:
It was here.

37:17.002 --> 37:19.037
Okay.
No, really, it was here.

37:19.070 --> 37:21.407
Today is trash Tuesday,
dickface.

37:33.519 --> 37:34.653
[***]

37:56.041 --> 37:59.878
I'm sorry, Charlie.
You were right.

38:03.014 --> 38:05.451
HENRY:
I don't get it.
How does it work?

38:05.484 --> 38:07.553
I don't know.
I'm not a scientist.

38:07.586 --> 38:09.355
All I know is that
it's spreading.

38:09.388 --> 38:10.756
I wonder if Bob Shulvock
is one of--

38:10.789 --> 38:12.057
Shh!

38:12.090 --> 38:13.559
He's got
three nipples.

38:13.592 --> 38:15.327
Shulvock has always
had three nipples.

38:15.361 --> 38:17.663
Yeah, but maybe it was
part of an advance team.

38:23.034 --> 38:24.403
[YAWNS]

38:24.436 --> 38:26.338
I'm worried about him.

38:26.372 --> 38:27.673
MATTHEW:
He's fine.

38:27.706 --> 38:30.976
Playing with his friends
in the neighborhood.

38:31.009 --> 38:35.714
It's not the first time he's
forgotten about the time, is it?

38:37.983 --> 38:41.453
Let's give it an hour.
If he doesn't show up,

38:41.487 --> 38:43.589
we'll drive around
the neighborhood.

38:56.968 --> 38:59.605
I've almost forgotten
what this is like.

39:01.640 --> 39:04.075
That thing's here
to try to bone your mom.

39:06.144 --> 39:07.546
CHARLIE:
We need to save her.

39:07.579 --> 39:09.748
We need to get him
away from her.

39:09.781 --> 39:11.116
How do we know
she's not like him?

39:11.149 --> 39:12.851
She's not.

39:12.884 --> 39:14.386
Yeah, but how do we know?

39:14.420 --> 39:15.887
Because she still
smells like my mom.

39:15.921 --> 39:17.456
Yeah, but--
She keeps telling me

39:17.489 --> 39:18.657
to pick up my clothes.

39:18.690 --> 39:20.091
Okay. She's your mom.

39:20.125 --> 39:21.893
[DOOR CREAKS]

39:27.666 --> 39:29.468
Okay.

39:29.501 --> 39:30.802
Let's do this.

39:30.836 --> 39:32.604
[FLASHLIGHT'S CLICK]

39:32.638 --> 39:36.174
[SLOW SONG PLAYING SOFTLY]

39:36.207 --> 39:41.880
* It makes no difference
Where I turn *

39:44.149 --> 39:48.654
* I can't get over you
And the flame still burns *

39:51.657 --> 39:53.091
* It makes no diff--

39:53.124 --> 39:54.460
[***]

39:59.565 --> 40:01.700
[***]

40:20.085 --> 40:21.853
Time's up, Charlie.

40:21.887 --> 40:24.956
I think I'm ready.

40:24.990 --> 40:27.859
But I'm really scared.

40:27.893 --> 40:29.861
You don't have
to be afraid.

40:31.563 --> 40:35.433
I told you, this is a real
opportunity for you.

40:51.149 --> 40:52.784
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

40:52.818 --> 40:54.753
Nice try, Charlie.

40:54.786 --> 40:57.923
[***]

41:04.663 --> 41:06.097
You lied to me, Charlie.

41:06.131 --> 41:07.533
Let him go!

41:07.566 --> 41:09.635
Oh!
[GASPS]

41:11.837 --> 41:13.104
Run!

41:15.907 --> 41:19.077
[***]

41:33.258 --> 41:34.860
Fuck.

41:42.568 --> 41:43.702
[GRUNTS]

41:51.309 --> 41:53.845
I know you're here,
Charlie.

41:55.981 --> 41:57.849
There's no use
in hiding.

41:59.685 --> 42:01.587
You're only making it
more difficult.

42:10.195 --> 42:12.798
[***]

42:36.722 --> 42:39.224
She's beautiful, isn't she?

42:39.257 --> 42:41.292
Leave us alone.

42:41.326 --> 42:43.028
Charlie,

42:43.061 --> 42:46.765
your mother and I will
always love you.

42:49.000 --> 42:52.638
And I will never
leave you.

42:52.671 --> 42:55.206
It'll be a lot easier
if you stop fighting.

42:55.240 --> 42:56.775
But you're not him.

42:59.878 --> 43:01.780
[***]

43:04.082 --> 43:05.216
[GROANS]

43:21.032 --> 43:22.167
Yeah!

43:40.819 --> 43:44.055
Oh, shit! Oh, shit!
Oh, shit!

43:44.089 --> 43:45.223
What the hell is that?

43:58.003 --> 43:59.971
Gotcha.

44:06.077 --> 44:07.212
[***]

44:47.819 --> 44:48.954
[SCREAMS]

44:53.424 --> 44:54.893
CHARLIE:
My best friend's brother Henry

44:54.926 --> 44:57.763
calls them
"dickheads from space."

44:57.796 --> 44:59.798
You okay?

44:59.831 --> 45:01.299
CHARLIE:
I don't know
where they come from,

45:01.332 --> 45:03.168
or what they want,

45:03.201 --> 45:05.470
but they have no right
to mess up our world.

45:07.205 --> 45:08.473
My father used to tell me that

45:08.506 --> 45:10.976
what made a person
is the insides.

45:11.009 --> 45:14.212
That it's the insides
that matter the most.

45:14.245 --> 45:16.181
Charlie.
[DOOR CLOSES]

45:19.284 --> 45:21.152
What happened to you?

45:21.186 --> 45:23.388
And when I would look
in my father's eyes,

45:23.421 --> 45:25.757
I could tell what kind
of a man he was.

45:25.791 --> 45:27.225
Where's your father?

45:27.258 --> 45:28.393
A good man.

45:30.796 --> 45:32.764
CHARLIE:
I took care of it, Mom.

45:32.798 --> 45:33.999
I took care
of everything.

45:36.301 --> 45:38.303
We'll fight them
in our homes,

45:38.336 --> 45:40.238
and we'll fight them
in our schools.

45:40.271 --> 45:44.509
We will never stop fighting,
and neither should you.

45:44.542 --> 45:46.912
I think my father
would be proud of me.

45:46.945 --> 45:48.947
[STATIC CRACKLES]

45:48.980 --> 45:51.482
[***]

45:59.490 --> 46:01.526
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

46:08.934 --> 46:11.837
[***]
